function keep_only_names(words)
    return filter(w -> w[1] == uppercasefirst(w[1]), words)
end
```

This function uses the `filter` built-in function to iterate over the list of words (`words`) and keep only those where the first letter is capitalized. The `uppercasefirst` function is used to normalize the case before comparison, ensuring a case-insensitive check.
